      "question": "Find the area of the shaded region in a circle of radius $14$ cm, where a sector subtends an angle of $60^{\\circ}$ at the center. (Use $\\pi = \\frac{22}{7}$)",
      "answer": "102.67 \\text{ cm}^2",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the formula for the area of a sector: $A = \\frac{\\theta}{360^{\\circ}} \\times \\pi r^2$",
          "Substitute the given values: $\\theta = 60^{\\circ}$, $r = 14$ cm, $\\pi = \\frac{22}{7}$",
          "Calculate the area: $A = \\frac{60}{360} \\times \\frac{22}{7} \times 14 \times 14 = \\frac{1}{6} \times 22 \times 2 \times 14$",
          "Simplify to get $\\frac{308}{3} \\approx 102.67 \\text{ cm}^2$"
        ],
        "derivation": "A = \\frac{60}{360} \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times 14^2 = \\frac{1}{6} \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times 196 = \\frac{1}{6} \\times 22 \\times 28 = \\frac{616}{6} = 102.67 \\text{ cm}^2"
      },
